Class ControllerHome

  • java.lang.Object
    • Controllers.ControllerHome

  • public class ControllerHome
extends java.lang.Object

      • validateLogin

        public boolean validateLogin(java.lang.String inputUsername,
                             java.lang.String inputPassword)
        The method checks if the username matches the password. If the user does not exist an error-message will appear. If the user is already logged in an error-message will appear. It will check salted and hashed password to the password which is written.
        Parameters:
        inputUsername - is a parameter which is used to identify the user.
        inputPassword - is a parameter which is used to compare the password to the user.
        Returns:
        true if username and password is validated.
